{
  "texts": [
    "With the U.S. producing 7,340 kg of cereal per hectare compared to the global average of 3,851 kg, the adoption of IoT devices in agriculture is expected to continue growing.",
    "Installations are projected to reach 75 million by 2020 (Singh et al. 2022).",
    "The use of precision sowing guided by artificial intelligence (AI) resulted in a 15% improvement in crop emergence rate compared to conventional approaches (Avalekar et al. 2024).",
    "Implementing AI-driven planting led to a 12% increase in agricultural productivity compared to traditional manual methods (Javaid et al. 2023).",
    "The use of AI to guide herbicide application resulted in a 40% decrease in weed biomass compared to the traditional method of human spraying (Márquez 2024)."
  ]
}